U.S. Secretary of Transportation Ray LaHood and Chief Economist to Vice President Biden Jared Bernstein will hold a media conference call to preview President Obama's visit to Columbus, Ohio on Friday, June 18. During his visit, the President will mark the groundbreaking of the 10,000th Recovery Act road project, which is expected to create over 300 new jobs and contribute to the economic development effort in the area around Nationwide Children's Hospital. The media conference call will take place on Thursday, June 17 at 3:15 PM EDT. Media interested in joining the call should dial (800) 230-1093 and ask to join the "White House Call."